=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Start from trans-4-hydroxy-L-proline methyl ester hydrochloride, neutralize the amine, then protect N with p-nitrobenzyl chloroformate (PNB-OCOCl) to give N-(p-nitrobenzyloxycarbonyl)-4-hydroxyproline methyl ester | Step 2: O-benzoylate the secondary alcohol with benzoyl chloride (or BzCl/DMAP, pyridine) to form the O-benzoyl, N-PNB-protected methyl ester intermediate | Step 3: Keep the stereodefined pyrrolidine core unchanged and retain the methyl ester during the orthogonal protection sequence, giving the fully protected methyl ester precursor | Step 4: Saponify the methyl ester with LiOH or NaOH in MeOH/H2O to the free carboxylic acid, furnishing the exact target O-benzoyl, N-(p-nitrobenzyloxycarbonyl) hydroxyproline derivative

